aa22-6c8b56eceb1d","name":"FG_23_002.jpg","version":"2.0","lastModifiedDate":1664998755,"lastSyncDate":1665085925},"source":{"small":{"width":557,"url":"https://assets-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/da967550-44e0-11ed-9967-59bbd5f34c83/small/534e21b0808d6fd63dd8337ce4b23abb.jpeg","height":300},"original":{"width":1113,"url":"https://assets-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/da967550-44e0-11ed-9967-59bbd5f34c83/medium/534e21b0808d6fd63dd8337ce4b23abb.jpeg","height":600},"medium":{"width":1113,"url":"https://assets-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/da967550-44e0-11ed-9967-59bbd5f34c83/medium/534e21b0808d6fd63dd8337ce4b23abb.jpeg","height":600},"thumb":{"width":278,"url":"https://assets-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/da967550-44e0-11ed-9967-59bbd5f34c83/thumb/534e21b0808d6fd63dd8337ce4b23abb.jpeg","height":150}},"metadata":{"altText":"","workURN":"","caption":"<p>This figure summarizes the transactions necessary to take advantage of the opportunity to make money by buying and selling McDonald&#x2019;s Big Macs at different prices around the world.</p>","alfrescoPath":"bronte-e2e-testing-qaint/documentLibrary/BV E2E Test/[10-05-2022] Berk","originalAssetName":"FG_23_002.jpg","longDesc":"","height":"431"}}},"alt":"","caption":"<p>This figure summarizes the transactions necessary to take advantage of the opportunity to make money by buying and selling McDonald&#x2019;s Big Macs at different prices around the world.</p>","layout":{"captionPosition":"Below"},"credit":"","activityLabel":"Figure 23.2","activityTitle":"McDonald&#x2019;s Big Macs Round-the-World Transactions","size":{"width":100}},"height":484,"ref":"7a16fd96-9064-4fd0-97f2-dbdf58f12eda"}],"ref":"5ea4b2d8-53c8-11ed-afa7-1bfab9b2dfd7"}],"ref":"5ea4b2d9-53c8-11ed-afa7-1bfab9b2dfd7"}],"rowsAreFullWidth":false,"backgroundImageUrl":"","cssClass":"","ref":"5ea4b2da-53c8-11ed-afa7-1bfab9b2dfd7","backgroundImageAltText":""}],"text":"23.1 Foreign Exchange In  Chapter 3 , we showed the following list of McDonald’s Big Mac prices, reproduced here in  Figure 23.1 . In  Chapter 3 , we pointed out that with free transportation, you would buy as many Big Macs as you could in Russia and try to sell them for a profit in Switzerland. But how would you do this? Assuming you are starting in the United States, you would need to exchange U.S. dollars for rubles to buy Big Macs in Russia. Then you would sell them in Switzerland, receiving Swiss Francs. Finally, for your profit, you would exchange those Swiss Francs into U.S. dollars again.  Figure 23.2  summarizes your transactions. As the figure indicates, you start by “buying” rubles with U.S. dollars. At first, buying money usually strikes students as odd, but that is exactly what happens every day in the foreign exchange markets—every currency has a price in terms of other currencies. Specifically, a  foreign exchange rate  is a price for a currency denominated in another currency. For example, it might cost you $1 to buy 70 rubles and $1.10 to buy 1 euro. Whereas you can buy small amounts of euros at any currency exchange such as those found in international airports, much larger sums of currencies are bought and sold around the clock on the  foreign exchange market .","ref":"5ea4b2db-53c8-11ed-afa7-1bfab9b2dfd7"},"screenType":"","transitions":{"enter":{"animation":"","duration":0,"easing":"","customKeyframes":""},"exit":{"animation":"","duration":0,"easing":"","customKeyframes":""}},"lockElements":false,"learnerCurrentAttempt":1,"footer":{"buttonText":"Next","buttonIcon":"Arrow","showFooter":false,"showHistoryNavButtons":false,"previewFooter":false,"position":"Fixed to screen bottom","footerComponent":{"showFooterDropArea":"hide","width":100,"footerComponentsAlignment":"right"}},"styles":{"background":{},"stage":{"maxWidth":940,"background":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","responsive":true,"padding":{"vertical":60,"horizontal":60},"border":{"color":"rgba(224, 224, 224, 1)","radius":0,"width":0}},"elements":{"padding":{"vertical":10,"horizontal":10}},"footer":{"buttonColor":"r